s_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aitchiss/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aitchiss/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}],"milestone":null,"comments":4,"created_at":"2022-01-12T11:41:13Z","updated_at":"2022-02-01T09:27:09Z","closed_at":"2022-02-01T09:27:09Z","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"Right now the \"Home\" link in the main navigation is hardcoded so Admins can't customize or remove it.\r\n\r\nIt's been reported by admins several time that they would like to be able to do something about it. Hence this issue.\r\n\r\nThe idea is to:\r\n1. Remove [hardcoded Home link](https://github.com/forem/forem/blob/main/app/views/layouts/_main_nav.html.erb#L6-L11).\r\n2. Add it back as a dynamically created link in admin's _Navigation_ section `/admin/customization/navigation_links`, on the 1st position.\r\n3. Make sure freshly setup Forems come with that link being added/prepopulated in _Navigation_.\r\n\r\nEven though step 2 might seem weird (i.e. _adding what we've just removed?!_) it is the way to not harm those who still want it while at the same time leaving a door to edit/remove if anyone needs to.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**FYI**\r\n\r\n- We've recently [done similar thing for \"Signup\" links](https://github.com/forem/forem/issues/15921).\r\n- Related Slack convos:\r\n    - [#pod-admin-experience thread](https://forem-team.slack.com/archives/C01S4QZUDNC/p1641913128078900).\r\n    - From private channel for @Amy: https://forem-team.slack.com/archives/C02DKQ56GU9/p1641373341126500?thread_ts=1641336411.122200&cid=C02DKQ56GU9\r\n\r\ncc'ing @Ridhwana @amywtlin @JennieOcken @nickytonline ","closed_by":{"login":"aitchiss","id":20773163,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIwNzczMTYz","avatar_url":"https